Installation
------------

1. Copy TPAPI dir to app.extensions
2. Add these lines to config/main.php
	'import'=>array(
		...
		'ext.TPAPI.*',
	),
	...
	'components'=>array(
		...
		// for simple authentication
		'api'=>array(
			'class'=>'ext.TPAPI.CTPerformant',
			'connection'=>array(
				'type'=>'simple',
				'user'=>'YOUR USERNAME',
				'pass'=>'YOUR PASSWORD',
				'api_url'=>'api.YOUR_NETWORK.COM',
			),
		),
		
		// for OAuth
		'tpapi'=>array(
			'class'=>'ext.TPAPI.CTPerformant',
			'connection'=>array(
				'type'=>'oauth',
				'key'=>'YOUR APP KEY',
				'secret'=>'YOUR APP SECRET',
				'instanceClass'=>'YourInstanceClass', // see below for details
			),
		),
	),

3. [For OAuth apps only. If you're using simple authentication, you're done.]

Register an app on http://apps.2performant.com/. Make sure to give it user read permission.

4. Copy the files in TPAPI/user to their appropriate locations in the application dir. E.g.
protected/extensions/TPAPI/user/controllers/AppController.php -> protected/controllers/AppController.php
protected/extensions/TPAPI/user/models/Instance.php -> protected/models/Instance.php
protected/extensions/TPAPI/user/models/Network.php -> protected/models/Network.php
 
 Feel free to rename the classes and their respective files according to the Yii Framework conventions.
 
5. Create a table to store instances based on the schema in TPAPI/user/data/instances.sql. Rename the table as you wish.

6. Do the same for the networks table in TPAPI/user/data/networks.sql
 
7. Modify the YourInstanceClass::tableName() and YourNetworkClass::tableName() methods according to the names of the tables you just created.

8. Modify the YourInstanceClass::networkClassName() method according to the name of the copy you created.

9. Modify 'Instance' in config/main.php components > api > connection > instanceClass according to the name of the class in the Instance.php copy you just made.

10. Modify key and secret in config/main.php components > api > connection


Usage
-----

Just call Yii::app()->tpapi->api_method($params) anywhere in the application.